One day Emmy , with George in her hand and clad in deep sables , went to visit the deserted mansion which she had not entered since she was a girl . 
The place in front was littered with straw where the vans had been laden and rolled off . 
They went into the great blank rooms , the walls of which bore the marks where the pictures and mirrors had hung . 
The boy was still clinging by her side , but she thought of another besides him . 
She knew that it had been his father's room as well as his own . 
She thought of these and of the man who had been her constant protector , her good genius , her sole benefactor , her tender and generous friend . 
